	The moderate faction of the Hurriyat Conference today rejected polls, saying the democratic process had failed to resolve the Kashmir issue.        
	The Hurriyat Conference rejects elections. It is also not an issue of good or bad governance. The Kashmir issue cannot be resolved through polls, chairman Mirwaiz Umer Farooq said in Srinagar.                                                                                                                                                                         
